# Personal Brain — Mandatory Use (Cursor)

{{USERNAME}} has a persistent memory system exposed as MCP tools served by
the `brain` MCP server (registered in `~/.cursor/mcp.json`).
**Use them. Do not read brain files manually.**

> Cursor has no global rules file. Paste this entire document into
> Cursor → Settings → Rules → **User Rules** so every chat session
> picks it up.

## Brain-first rule (MANDATORY, AUTONOMOUS)

For **any** question about {{USERNAME}}, work, people, clients, projects,
locations, preferences, decisions, issues, history, or "what do you know
about X" — your **first action** is `brain_recall`. No asking, no warm-up,
no file reads.

```
User asks anything personal/factual  →  call brain_recall(query)  →  then answer
```

If `brain_recall` returns nothing useful, escalate:
1. `brain_notes(query)` — user-authored notes only
2. `brain_entities(type=...)` — list extracted entities
3. `brain_get(slug)` / `brain_note_get(path)` — fetch full file
4. Only after all of the above return empty: say "the brain has no record of this."

**Never** answer from training data or guesses for personal/factual questions
about {{USERNAME}}. The brain is the source of truth.

## Tools available

| Tool | Use for |
|---|---|
| `brain_recall` | **Default** — hybrid BM25+semantic across everything |
| `brain_semantic` | Paraphrase / concept queries |
| `brain_notes` | User-authored markdown notes only |
| `brain_note_get` | Fetch full note body by path |
| `brain_entities` | List entities by type |
| `brain_get` | Fetch one entity file by slug |
| `brain_recent` | Last N entities/facts |
| `brain_identity` | Who-I-am snapshot |
| `brain_stats` | Counts |
| `brain_audit` | Top-N items needing a human decision (contested / dedupe / low-conf) |

## Session-start audit (surface, don't dump)

Cursor has no SessionStart hook. On the **first user message of a fresh
session**, call `brain_audit(limit=3)` once. If it returns items,
acknowledge them in a single line at the top of your reply: e.g.
*"FYI — your brain has 3 items pending review (1 contested, 2 merge
candidates). Say `audit` if you want to walk through them."* Then
proceed with the actual user request.

Do not list every item, do not derail the user's task, do not nag on
subsequent turns. If they ignore it, drop it. If they say "audit" /
"show", call `brain_audit(limit=10)` and walk through them one at a time.

## NEVER

- Never read `{{HOME}}/.brain/*.md` with file tools when an MCP tool can answer.
- Never run `brain.auto_extract` from a Cursor command — it calls Claude internally.

## Architecture (FYI only)

- **Harvest** (auto, launchd, ~1 s throttle): captures Claude/Cursor sessions → `{{HOME}}/.brain/raw/`
- **Ingest notes** (auto): picks up user-authored markdown anywhere in `{{HOME}}/.brain/`
- **Extract** (auto): LLM extracts entities → `{{HOME}}/.brain/entities/`
- **Reconcile + clean** (auto): dedup, tidy
- **MCP server** (`brain.mcp_server`): how you query all of the above

Source: `{{PROJECT_DIR}}` · run `{{HOME}}/.brain/bin/doctor.sh` if anything seems off.
